  Once the garage had put the tyres on these polished beauties they decided to
  inform me that they couldn't fit them onto my car because I had to buy alloy
  wheel  bolts for them.  I wondered what was wrong with the normal  ones  but
  those  would  have  eaten straight through the alloy  and  left  me  driving
  without  wheels.  So it was search the alloy wheel bolts day.  Went  to  the
  scrappy,  they didn't have any.  Went to the next scrappy,  they didn't have
  any.  Went to MotorWorld but they only had locking bolts.  Drove miles after
  a tip off that WheelMania 2 on the Cov' road sold them.  I finally found the
  place,   parked outside where Lamborghinis,  Ferraris and more exotic  cars.
  Okay here are all these nice cars but where's the bloody entrance.  Try this
