  back  to  the  garage where my alloys where waiting for  me.   They  fitted,
  balanced and tracked them and that was that.  I still have those alloys  on,
  it  improves  grip around corners as they are wider wheels  but  since  they
  have  low profile tyres it is a rougher ride over bumps etc,  they  do  look
  the bizz tho'.

  Now  it  was time to go inside the car and onto my favourite thing in  life.
  MUSIC!   I  bought a 300W amp and a 400W 12" sub to go on the MDF  backshelf
  with  2 6X9s already on it and another two mid range speakers to go  in  the
  front.  It took a while to set up and I blew quite a few fuses but the  bass
  was  there  and  that's  what really matters. I had people  dancing  on  the
  street,   I shit you not,  I was driving home from work blaring out  Clarkee
  and  this  guy  waiting to cross the street heard me coming and  started  to
  dance to the music.  I laughed so loud I almost crashed the car. So here was
  my  red  birdmobile  that everyone loved and envied but  the  MOT  date  was
  getting  closer and it was always in the back of my mind.   Don't  worry  it
  only failed on a wiper blade last time it will be fine I thought.
