          "Oh I see. So I've completely wasted a day just to hear this."
  @2
                       "Sorry but that's the way it goes."
  @5
  At  that point another young cocky mechanic came up to defend his  toothless
  mate.  I left blaring out the whole garage with Drum and Bass from my stereo
  and smoke from my wheels. What a wanker though!

  When  I  got  home  I phoned up my brother in law and he said  that  he  was
  completely  different when he knew him.  He gave a person in Surrey  a  ring
  who  owned  a garage and explained the situation.  I could get it  done  for
  £200  but I'd have to drive it down to Surrey with no MOT.  Why not.  I  set
  out at 6AM and arrived at my Brother in laws house in Enfield at 8:30AM.   I
  got  them  out of bed.  After I'd got in and relaxed a bit it  was  time  to
  move,  Meadvale awaits us.  After dropping my sis' off at work we flew  down
  the  M25,   through the Dartford tunnel and finally into Meadvale  at  about
  10AM.  We got to a tiny garage on the top of a hill, and I was surprised. It
  really  didn't  look like a garage,  it was really cramped  and  had  a  few
  little  out  buildings.  Rob and Caroline who owned it were really  friendly
  and  were impressed at the Alloy wheels I had put on it.  It was off to work
  they  go.  First they cleaned up the battery tray and pulled the rotton  one
  out.  Upon removal of the battery I saw the carpet inside the car. This rust
  hole  had  the  power leads to my amp running through them so I disconnected
  that and they plugged the hole up by welding bits of metal to it.  It took a
  lot  longer  than  I  thought.  They had to get under  the  wheel  arch  and
  everything.  Meanwhile me and my bro' were relaxing with a pint in the White
  Lion.   After a few games of pool we descided to head back in  the  freezing
  wind  to  see how they were doing.  They had just finished welding  the  new@5
  battery  tray  on  and  were  in the process of removing  the  rotton  sill.
  Sudden panic hit me,  this was a one off paint job which coincidentally they
  did,   how were they going to match the paint? Well it turned out that  they
  painted both of the sills black so it didn't look odd.

  Great,  I thought I might just get home tonight and get the MOT tomorow. Not
  so fast,  disaster struck.  Upon lifting the carpet up inside the car we saw
  a nice gaping hole,  I was surprised that the seat wasn't falling out.  That
  set  us  back  another two days but it was well worth it in the  end.   They
  MOT'd  my  car at a local garage and it passed with flying colours.  Nothing
  wrong  with  the  emmisions or the steering rack so F**K YOU  Baldwins  Lane
  Station.  Well in the end it only cost me £160 and about £50 in petrol so  I
  made  a  huge  saving.  We finally finished the car up at  00:00  on  Sunday
  morning.   I drove the car back to Enfield as everyone else was  pissed.   I
  think they deserved it after all that work.



  @5
  Coming back on the M25 at 1AM I thought I might test this baby out.  It took
  a  while  but  I  got  up to a maximum speed of 110 MPH  in  the  fast  lane
  of course.  I  only  slowed down when we got to the Dartford  tunnel.   Upon
  arrival home I tried to figure out how to reconnect the Amp.  In the  end  I
  pulled  the cigar lighter out@1 (I didn't smoke anyway)@5  and tapped the  power
  off  that.   The  only wierd thing was - when I put the lights  on  the  amp
  switched  off.  I still haven't figured it out.  To make my car  even  nicer
  looking with black sills I bought a blue interior lamp.  Unfortunately  that
  stopped  working as well so I had some electrical problems to say the least.
  Was it the Amp,  the stereo or the 7 speakers? Who knows,  at least I had an
  MOT.

  I'm very sorry to say that I have driven while over the limit once. It was a
  night I split up with my girlfriend so I wasn't in the mood for reconing.  I
  knew  it was wrong and when I started the engine it felt alien to be in  the
  car.  Luckily I got home in one piece,  I don't recommend anyone try it. But
  for  anyone  who  takes drugs,  remember that illegal  drugs  can  have  bad
  affects on your driving aswell.

  Well  there  you have it.  That was my first car and it still is  because  I
  have  no intention of getting rid of it yet.  I just hope it does better  on
  it's  next MOT.  As far as general driving goes,  I have had plenty of  near
  misses.  People pulling out on you at the last second,  cutting you up, it's
  scary  if you  lock your brakes up in the wet,  but luckily  I  haven't  hit
  anyone or anything.
  ]5@3
